---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { href } from '../../i18n/ui';

const email = 'raphael@plumservices.co';
const updated = '18 July 2026';
---

<Base
  lang="en"
  routeKey="terms"
  title="Terms of use — Sereno"
  description="Sereno’s terms: free forever, voluntary Stripe support, your data stays yours."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h1>Terms of use</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>
      <p>
        These terms govern use of the Sereno application and website.
      </p>

      <h2>1. The service</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno is a personal budgeting app with manual entry. It works without
        an account (local data) and offers an optional free account for
        cross-device sync. No artificial-intelligence features (receipt OCR
        scanning, opaque auto-categorization, etc.) are offered.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Free forever &amp; voluntary support</h2>
      <p>
        The service is <strong>free forever</strong>: guest mode and sync
        account, with no ads and no commercial exploitation of your data. No
        paid plan gates features. <strong>Voluntary support</strong> (one-time
        donation) may be offered via Stripe Payment Links on the
        <a href={href('en', 'support')}>Support</a> page; it is never required
        and unlocks no paid “tier.”
      </p>

      <h2>3. Your account</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for keeping your credentials confidential. Notify us
        promptly of unauthorized use. Minimum age with an account is 15.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Your data</h2>
      <p>
        Data you enter belongs to you. You may export it anytime and request
        account deletion (see the
        <a href={href('en', 'privacy')}>privacy policy</a>).
      </p>

      <h2>5. Not financial advice</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno shows totals, breakdowns, and projections from what you enter.
        These are readability tools,
        <strong>not financial, tax, or investment advice</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to compromise the service: no unauthorized access to other
        users’ data, no deliberate overload, no illegal use.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Availability &amp; changes</h2>
      <p>
        Sereno is an independent project provided “as is.” Features may evolve;
        if sync is discontinued, reasonable notice and export options will be
        given. Local mode depends on no server.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the extent permitted by law, the publisher is not liable for
        indirect damages from using the service. Nothing excludes liability for
        gross negligence or willful misconduct.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        French law. Amicable resolution sought before litigation; otherwise
        French courts have jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
